36:12.504 --> 36:16.541 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Almost every single person in
every tiny town
in Mexico knows who Kate del
Castillo is.

36:16.574 --> 36:20.712 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: But take on
this issue.
You're a journalist. You have
covered this

36:20.745 --> 36:24.115 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
story many, many years. You
teach young journalists.

36:24.149 --> 36:27.819 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Is there a circumstance that you
would ever
have agreed to these types of
conditions,

36:27.852 --> 36:32.290 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to let an actor go and interview
a kingpin
under these circumstances, with
these kind

36:32.323 --> 36:33.758 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of conditions put on it?

36:33.792 --> 36:37.195 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ANGELA KOCHERGA: I don't think
it's a -- we
would call it journalism.

36:37.228 --> 36:41.599 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You would call it a conversation
between an
actor and a drug lord. And that,
in and of

36:41.633 --> 36:44.436 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
itself, the story behind the
story, is fascinating,
how they came together.

36:44.469 --> 36:49.607 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But we also have to remember,
